Bootstrap Templating Kit for Magnolia CMS

Bootstrap is an open source toolkit for developing with HTML, CSS, and JS. Quickly prototype your ideas or build your entire app with our Sass variables and mixins, responsive grid system, extensive prebuilt components, and powerful plugins built on jQuery.

Magnolia CMS lets you create timely, relevant and consistent interactions with your customers that drive real results: accelerate lead conversion, increase sales, strengthen your brand, and engage your customers on the channels they use. Drive diverse business goals with one powerful platform.

BTK is a light module for Magnolia CMS with a basic set of templates ideal to start new website project based on Bootstrap framework.

It contains most basic components as well as row component allowing you to take advantage of Bootstrap grid.

The module contains also few page examples.

The module is also a great way of learning how to build Magnolia templates.

Built with Bootstrap Templating Kit for Magnolia CMS by the Magnolia team.

List of available page types.

All pages consist auto generated top navigation bar.

Page and Search types consist also auto generated breadcrumb under the navigation bar.

Home page is a type usually used for root page.

It is unique in the way that it contains header area in which user can add header specific components: Jumbotron and/or Carousel.

All not Home type children of the page will inherit the footer set in the Home page.
Go to Home with Jumbotron example
Go to Home with Carousel example

Page is basic page type. Used for any subpage content.

Component or this pages are examples of Page type page.

Search type is a special page type. It is used to render the results of search in all pages of the website.

Search input in navigation is added only if Search page is created and set as child of the root page.

Type “button” in the top right hand side search input and click Search button to see the example of Search page.
